data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nrq1665703527989.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nrq1665703527989.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nrq1665703527989.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nrq1665703527989\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Change the value of a field, variable, or watch expression. Specify a new value for\n      the field, variable or watch. Then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Apply</span> or\n         <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Close</span>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__section_z5c_ghh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d255128e60\">Field, Variable, or Watch fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Displays the name of the field, variable, or watch value to edit. This is a read-only\n            field.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__section_mz2_lhh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d255128e69\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Expression</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Value</span></h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__ul_m4w_mhh_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__li_d53489e1_d53490e1_d53491e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Expression</span>—name of the field, variable, or watch value to\n               edit. This is a read-only field.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__li_d53492e1_d53493e1_d53494e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Value</span>—current value of the field, variable, or watch and\n               allows you to edit it.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__section_ohg_3hh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d255128e94\">Buttons</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__ul_ls5_shh_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Apply</span>—applies a change to a value.</li>\n<li class=\"li\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Close</span>—applies any changes and exits the form.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nrq1665703527989__section_gz4_qhh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d255128e113\">Editing</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">To edit the fields, refer to <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vsb1665703523691.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vsb1665703523691.html\" title=\"Update watch fields, variables, or values.\">Updating fields, variables, or watch values</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/epv1665703523533.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with watches</a><p>Add watches from the debugger main window or from the browser.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gjf1665702773980.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Browsing ProcScript Modules in the Uniface Debugger</a><p>Navigate to specific ProcScript modules in components or global ProcScript using the Debugger Browser, and use the browser to set breakpoints and watches.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530397\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530397\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Fields, Variables, or Watches Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Change the value of a field, variable, or watch expression. Specify a new value for the field, variable or watch. Then click Apply or Close . Field, Variable, or Watch fields Displays the name of the field, variable, or watch value to edit. This is a read-only field. Expression and Value Expression —name of the field, variable, or watch value to edit. This is a read-only field. Value —current value of the field, variable, or watch and allows you to edit it. Buttons Apply —applies a change to a value. Close —applies any changes and exits the form. Editing To edit the fields, refer to Updating fields, variables, or watch values . Related Links Working with watches Add watches from the debugger main window or from the browser. Browsing ProcScript Modules in the Uniface Debugger Navigate to specific ProcScript modules in components or global ProcScript using the Debugger Browser, and use the browser to set breakpoints and watches. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}